news.title: Government directs House of Abhinandan Lodha to withdraw 'Conquer Goa' ad
news.para: “I am directed to inform you that it has been brought to the notice of this department that The House of Abhinandan Lodha group has published the advertisement captioned ‘Delhi, Rulers of India, Now Conquer Goa’,” Manesh Kedar, under secretary (home department), said in a letter to the manager of the developer.

news.title: Singapore government, others buys PNB Housing Finance shares worth Rs 178 crore
news.para: According to the block deal data available on the NSE, the Singapore government bought 13.16 lakh shares, the Monetary Authority of Singapore purchased 2.13 lakh scrips, and Goldman Sachs (Singapore) picked up 92,000 units of PNB Housing Finance.

news.title: Puravankara to redevelop Miami Apartments in South Mumbai
news.para: In Bengaluru, Puravankara has signed a joint development agreement (JDA) for a 1.95-acre land parcel in Electronics City. This land parcel will have a saleable area of 2.6 lakh sq ft.

news.title: Raymond to invest Rs 100 crore in Ten X Realty West
news.para: Raymond's board has also approved to invest an amount up to Rs 50 crore in the form of redeemable preference shares in one or more tranches in Ten X Realty (TXRL), a step down wholly owned subsidiary of the company.

news.title: Vastu Housing Finance looking to raise up to $50 million from US IDFC
news.para: Money raised from the route will be deployed for enhancing credit access for low-income borrowers, focusing on fulfilling housing needs and encouraging women's home ownership in Tier II to IV towns across India.

news.title: Birla Estates buys 24.5 acre land in Mumbai for Rs 537.42 crore
news.para: "The registration document, reviewed by Square Yards, indicates that Ekamaya Property Pvt Ltd, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Birla Estates Private Limited, acquired the 99,021.47 square meter (~24.5 acres) land parcel," the company said in a statement.

news.title: Noida: Unitech's housing projects to resume construction under new board
news.para: Allotted land in 2006, Express City (UGCC Grande) initially included three residential projects — Amber and Burgundy (group housing), and The Willows 1 and 2, which had plots for sale. While the two housing projects had 638 buyers, 360 people had booked plots in Willow. A total of 818 flats was sanctioned in the housing projects, while another 180 acres remained vacant.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh RERA opposes EOW probe into corruption allegations against chairman
news.para: EOW had recently initiated a preliminary inquiry to probe an alleged complaint of corruption, misuse of official position, and regulatory violations against Srivastava.

news.title: NCLT approves acquisition of Radius Estates by Adani Group’s Bridgeport Realtors
news.para: ​​This plan was previously approved by the NCLT in January 2023, as part of a broader strategy to revive and consolidate the operations of Radius Estates. The resolution plan was proposed by Adani Goodhomes and the same had also been validated by the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT) in May 2024.

news.title: NBCC to develop housing, commercial spaces worth Rs 1,600 crore on MTNL's land in Delhi
news.para: ​​ In a statement on Thursday, NBCC said that it has signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd (MTNL) to collaborate and "develop a prominent land parcel of MTNL measuring approximately 13.88 acres located on Pankha Road, New Delhi."

news.title: Fitch lowers China Vanke's issuer ratings to 'B+' from 'BB-'
news.para: The downgrade reflects ongoing pressure on China Vanke's liquidity due to lower-than-expected sales and cash flow generation in the first half of 2024, the ratings agency said, adding that the company's liquidity buffer was diminishing.

news.title: China Evergrande' chairman kept in special detention center in Shenzhen: Sources
news.para: Hui, 65, has not been seen in public since he was taken away by Chinese authorities a year ago and his current whereabouts have not been previously reported.

news.title: 315Work Avenue leases 56,000 sq ft office space in International Tech Park, Pune
news.para: Earlier, the company had leased 44,000 sq ft at ITPP. ITPP is a Grade A, 2.5 million sq ft tech Park, developed by Ascendas-Singbridge,

news.title: hBits launches Rs 28.8 crore asset in Vaswani Centropolis, Bengaluru
news.para: The asset spans across a leasable area of 12,776 sq ft and has been leased for a period of six years. The rental inflow and purchase price of the asset offers an entry yield of 8.75% and an expected internal rate of return of 15.12%.

news.title: Sumadhura Group lease out 1.8 lakh sq ft space to Nippon Express in Bengaluru
news.para: The company is investing Rs 600 crore in the first phase of Sumadhura Logistics Park, which covers around 100 acres of land and offers 2.5 million sq ft of commercial warehousing space.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: MPIDC to develop residential blocks in industrial areas
news.para: The industry department is currently formulating plans to construct residential blocks at Vikram Udhyogpuri industrial area in Ujjain and Mandideep industrial area in Bhopal.

news.title: Pune: Uruli Devachi, Phursungi to get separate municipal council
news.para: State govt on Wednesday issued a final notification to exclude these areas from PMC limits, and to constitute a separate joint Phursungi Uruli Devachi Municipal Council.

news.title: Around 18,000 properties in Pune civic body's merged areas remain untaxed
news.para: "The administration has come across 45 officials who have not done their duties properly. The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) will act against these officials for dereliction of duty. A fine equal to a month's salary will be charged," said a senior official of PMC.

news.title: Government extends OTS scheme for property tax defaulters in Bengaluru
news.para: This is the second time the govt has extended the scheme. Property taxpayers can now clear their dues under the scheme till Nov 30. The govt had introduced OTS in Feb this year, and the scheme expired on July 31. Later, the govt extended it till Sept 30.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body razes 35 illegal structures
news.para: The drive was undertaken near Hid Park and Masjid-e-Abeda, where unauthorized residential row houses and commercial units were coming up.
